quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Compassionate (Allah)
  55,2,Who taught the Qur’an
  55,3,created man
  55,4,and taught him how to convey his feelings and thoughts
  55,5,The sun and the moon move along their computed courses
  55,6,The shrubs and the trees prostrate in adoration
  55,7,He has raised the heaven on high and created the balance
  55,8,don’t ever tamper with this balance
  55,9,"Therefore, you also establish weight with justice and do not give less measure"
  55,10,He laid out the earth for His creatures
  55,11,with all its fruits and palms having sheathed clusters
  55,12,and grain with husk and scented herbs
  55,13,"So, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,14,He created man from sounding clay similar to pottery
  55,15,and created jinns from smokeless fire
  55,16,"So, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,17,He is Lord of the two easts and the Lord of the two wests
  55,18,"So, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,19,He has made the two oceans apparently meeting together
  55,20,yet between them is a barrier which they cannot cross
  55,21,"So, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,22,He produces pearls and coral from both of them
  55,23,"So, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"
  55,24,His are the ships looming up like mountains on the sea
  55,25,"So, O jinn and men, which of your Lord’s favors will both of you deny"